<TITLE> President, CA renew calls for a true democratic society </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 25 (bdnews24.com)President Iajuddin Ahmed and chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Tuesday paid homage to Liberation War martyrs and renewed calls to build a "true democratic society". In a message on Independence and National Day, Iajuddin said: "The historic Independence and National Day is a glorious day in our national life. I recall with deep respects and pay homage to the martyrs of the Liberation War who made supreme sacrifices for our independence in 1971." "I also pay my profound respects and gratitude to the valiant freedom fighters, organisers of the Liberation War and people from all walks of life who rendered their dedicated efforts and extended enthusiastic support that expedited the achievement of our long-cherished independence." The president urged all citizens, living at home and abroad, to work together with continued efforts to expedite overall economic self-reliance and democratic advancement. In a separate message, Fakhruddin said: "The glorious liberation is our greatest national achievement. For this achievement to be meaningful, sustainable and effective, it is very important to bring the fruits of the independence to all citizens." "It is equally important to establish social justice and good governance and to improve the living conditions of the people. Establishing a modern, progressive and exploitation-free democratic country is the demand of the day," he said. "To achieve this, we should play due roles from our respective positions with dedication, sincerity and honesty, imbued with the spirit of Liberation War and patriotism," the CA said. bd
